Description: Made of brass, this Geberit Mapress 22 x 22mm lever-operated ball valve is fitted with press-fit connections. Title: JET Range 56 wheel head gate valve (BSP) PN20 40mm Brass
Description: This JET Range 56 gate valve is designed for isolating pipelines. With 40mm BSP tapered female connections, the valve includes a brass body, wedge, screwed bonnet, non-rising stem and wheel handle. A gate valve, also known as a sluice valve, opens by lifting a barrier out of the path of a fluid. Gate valves normally require minimal space along the pipe axis and offer minimal flow restriction when fully open. A multiturn valve, operation of a gate valve is carried out via a threaded stem, turning multiple times to change position.

Title: Crane Butterfly Valves F624 lever operated butterfly valve PN16 2"
Description: Suitable for applications requiring Level 3 C3 (medium) corrosion protection, this maintenance-free Crane F624 fully-lugged PN16 butterfly valve incorporates 2" connections and a ductile iron body. It is part of an extensive multilayer pipe system that blends the convenience of synthetics with the robustness of metal for a flexible, hygienic and hardwearing potable water solution that's also suitable for radiator connections. Complying with hygiene standards, the complete system can be installed without prior water analysis and is supplied with protective plugs for removal during installation, providing further protection from contamination. Geberit multilayer pipes are manufactured with a protective PE-RT outer layer that resists corrosion and mechanical damage. Inside, an aluminium middle layer provides stability, flexibility and provides a barrier against diffusion, while the inner PR-RT layer is corrosion resistant and food safe.

Title: Geberit FlowFit 620.310.00.1 Male adaptor 16mm x 1/2"
Description: Part of a comprehensive system, this Geberit FlowFit 16mm x 1/2" male adapter is made of polyphenylsulfone (PPSU) and fitted with press-fit connections. Developed with the input of the plumbers who will use it, the innovative FlowFit system ensures always-right installation, for a simpler job on-site with no need for deburring and calibration when cutting to length and the ability to laterally press and rotate for convenient and reliable pressing in difficult spots with no risk of contortion. This system is compatible with both cold and hot potable water, cooling and heating water with or without antifreeze agent and with service water and process water. It can also be used in treated water, rainwater with a pH value of <gt/>6, seawater and extinguishing water (wet, wet/dry or dry). It is also suitable for chemicals and technical liquids, compressed air (oil purity class 0–3), inert gases such as nitrogen and in negative pressure. FlowFit is suitable for a variety of applications, including technical building

Title: Center CB 635862 90deg integral solder ring street elbow 28mm
Description: Compact and lightweight, this Center CB internal solder ring (ISR) 90° street elbow with 28mm connections is designed for ease of handling and straightforward installation, even in awkward spaces. A smooth design helps to minimise flow restrictions while also ensuring it looks neat when installed on exposed pipelines. Precision-made, the ISR incorporates best-quality solder in each capillary socket, ready to create a reliable joint with no need to end feed. A solder joint is created through the principle of capillary action. When fitting and tube are heated to the correct temperature, the solder becomes molten, allowing it to be drawn into the gap between the two for a tough, reliable joint.

Description: The Hattersley Fig 100 lever operated ball valve is easy to install, compact and lightweight and is supplied with 20mm BSP tapered connections. Made of DZR brass, this robust valve offers full flow with minimum turbulence in the open position and bubble tight closure in the closed position. A ball valve is a type of quarter-turn valve featuring a hollow, perforated ball that pivots to control the flow of a fluid. Description: The compact and light Crane D171 bronze manual ball valve is simple to install and operate, offering 32mm connections and lever operation. This valve provides full flow with minimum turbulence in the open position and a bubble-tight seal in the closed position. A ball valve is a type of quarter-turn valve featuring a hollow, perforated ball that pivots to control the flow of a fluid. Title: Geberit m of flowfit pipe 50mm in 5m length
Description: This Geberit FlowFit 50mm pipe is supplied in a 5M length. It is part of an extensive multilayer pipe system that blends the convenience of synthetics with the robustness of metal for a flexible, hygienic and hardwearing potable water solution that's also suitable for radiator connections. Geberit multilayer pipes are manufactured with a protective PE-RT outer layer that resists corrosion and mechanical damage. Inside, an aluminium middle layer provides stability, flexibility and provides a barrier against diffusion, while the inner PR-RT layer is corrosion resistant and food safe.
